# DGX sync reminder (after code changes)

Whenever you **create, edit, or delete** files under this repo, **apply scp sync yourself** after the edit (user permission). **Never** run git push/pull/fetch/upstream unless the user explicitly asks.

## Agent behavior (DGX)

1. **Do the work on DGX** (edit, prune, `npm install`, restart API, etc.).
2. **Do not** run `git push`, `git pull`, `git fetch`, or merge `upstream` unless the user explicitly asks.
3. **After DGX-owned changes** — run automatically when Surface SSH works:
   ```bash
   cd /home/sifr/OpenNexus3DStudio
   bash scripts/sync-to-pc.sh
   ```
   Use `--include-src` only when `src/` was edited on DGX (lock first per sync rules).
   After milestones, also push agent context:
   ```bash
   bash scripts/sync-to-pc.sh --include-agent-context
   bash scripts/sync-sessionmem-team.sh
   ```
4. **Run `bash scripts/ensure-dgx-sync-ready.sh`** after PC→DGX syncs or doc cleanup.
5. **Do not** nag about sync if you already ran it. Only report if sync **failed**.

## Ownership (which script)

| Changed files | Source of truth | Run on **Surface (PC)** |
| ------------- | --------------- | ----------------------- |
| `src/`, scripts, roadmaps | PC | `.\scripts\sync-to-dgx.ps1` |
| Pitch Deck, README, package.json, docs | DGX | `.\scripts\sync-from-dgx.ps1` |
| sync-*.ps1, prune-sync-duplicates.sh | DGX | `.\scripts\sync-from-dgx.ps1` |

**Important:** `sync-from-dgx.ps1` does **not** copy `src/` or roadmaps. If you
edited `src/` on **DGX (Cursor Remote)**, push to Surface before the user can
test in the browser:

```bash
cd /home/sifr/OpenNexus3DStudio
bash scripts/sync-to-pc.sh --include-src
bash scripts/sync-to-pc.sh --include-agent-context   # memory-bank + graphify-out
bash scripts/sync-sessionmem-team.sh               # SessionMem team folder
```

Requires OpenSSH on Surface (port 22). Surface has a matching rule:
`.cursor/rules/surface-sync-reminder.mdc`.

## Scripts (PowerShell, from Surface repo root)

```powershell
# Pull DGX-owned docs/branding + sync workflow scripts
.\scripts\sync-from-dgx.ps1

# Push PC code + MONETIZATION_ROADMAP.md → DGX (runs ensure on DGX)
.\scripts\sync-to-dgx.ps1

# Wrapper
.\scripts\sync-dgx.ps1 -Direction from-dgx
.\scripts\sync-dgx.ps1 -Direction to-dgx

# Away from home LAN
.\scripts\sync-from-dgx.ps1 -Remote
.\scripts\sync-to-dgx.ps1 -Remote
```

## Optional (on DGX, after PC push)

```bash
cd /home/sifr/OpenNexus3DStudio
bash scripts/ensure-dgx-sync-ready.sh
```

Push DGX-owned files to Surface when Surface SSH is enabled:

```bash
bash scripts/sync-to-pc.sh
```

## Backend (`3DAIGC-API`)

API changes on DGX take effect after restart on Spark (`:7842`). No PC sync
script — frontend reaches API via `VITE_API_ENDPOINT=/__dev_dgx_proxy` →
`http://10.0.0.158:7842`.

Surface agent rule (local PC): `.cursor/rules/surface-sync-reminder.mdc`

## Equal role on DGX

DGX agent has the **same execute permissions** as Surface: edit files, run `sync-to-pc.sh` automatically after edits, SSH to Surface when needed. Never offer options — do it or report a blocker.
